verses.roman:
tabe prabhu prasādānna govinda-hāte dilā
yatna kari' haridāsa-ṭhākure pāṭhāilā

synonyms: tabe—thereafter; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; prasāda-anna—remnants of Jagannātha's food; govinda-hāte—in the hand of Govinda; dilā—delivered; yatna kari'—with great attention; haridāsa-ṭhākure—unto Haridāsa Ṭhākura; pāṭhāilā—sent.
translation: After this, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu carefully delivered some prasāda into the hands of Govinda to be given to Haridāsa Ṭhākura.
